<item>
            <title>[PIG-960] Using Hadoop&apos;s optimized LineRecordReader for reading Tuples in PigStorage </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-960</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;PigStorage&apos;s reading of Tuples ( lines ) can be optimized using Hadoop&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;LineRecordReader&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can help in following areas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Improving performance reading of Tuples (lines) in &lt;tt&gt;PigStorage&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Any future improvements in line reading done in Hadoop&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;LineRecordReader&lt;/tt&gt; is automatically carried over to Pig&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Issues that are handled by this patch&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;BZip uses internal buffers and positioning for determining the number of bytes read. Hence buffering done by &lt;tt&gt;LineRecordReader&lt;/tt&gt; has to be turned off&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Current implementation of &lt;tt&gt;LocalSeekableInputStream&lt;/tt&gt; does not implement &lt;tt&gt;available&lt;/tt&gt; method. This method has to be implemented.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
