                            <comment id="12760792" author="daijy" created="Wed, 30 Sep 2009 01:48:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Couple of comments:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Why PigLineRecordReader inherits BufferedPositionedInputStream? Shouldn&apos;t it just be a wrapper?&lt;br/&gt;
2. In PigStorage.skip, you do not count line delimit when skipping?&lt;br/&gt;
3. Why not add a test case for skip?&lt;br/&gt;
4. Two typos &quot;Excpected&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12760822" author="ankit.modi" created="Wed, 30 Sep 2009 04:15:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for comments Daniel.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Answers:&lt;br/&gt;
1. PigLineRecordReader (PLRR) needs to know the type of InputStream it is handling. BZip2 or Uncompressed. Depending on the type of input stream it chooses which Reader to utilize. BPIS ( BufferedPositionedInputStream ) stores the input stream as a protected member. PLRR can access this via following ways: - making member public, - adding a get method to access it or - inherit.&lt;br/&gt;
I implemented the last one as it makes least changes to BPIS.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Good one. Will be fixed in next patch.&lt;br/&gt;
3. Will be added in next patch&lt;br/&gt;
4. Corrected in next patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
